OL,4,CCouncils hit by bin collection delays
OL,5,Cdue to driver shortage
OL,6, At least 18 councils across the UK
OL,7, confirmed on Thursday that they are
OL,8, experiencing ongoing disruptions to
OL,9, their bin collection services.
OL,11,FIt is due to staff self-isolating and a
OL,12,Flack of heavy goods vehicle (HGV)
OL,13,Fdrivers who can drive bin lorries.
OL,15,FThe Local Government Association (LGA)
OL,16,Ftold the BBC that the delays were
OL,17,Fprimarily affecting garden waste.
OL,19,FHowever, some councils are also
OL,20,Fdelaying recycling collections in order
OL,21,Fto prioritise general waste.
